author: 滇西小哥 Dianxi Xiaoge
description:
※Click "cc" on the lower right menu to choose your subtitle language.

There’s barely any space in our home garden and no way to expand it, but I love flowers and plants so much that I end up redoing it every year. This time, I picked up some flowers at the market—cheap, lively, and blooming beautifully—to replace all the withered branches and fallen leaves at home.
Grandma always likes to grow all kinds of vegetables in the flower beds. This time, we dug out a lot of fish mint, and I made sure she ate it all in one go—just to stop her from secretly planting it back again!

Hello, everyone! I am Dianxi Xiaoge, a Yunnan native. If you enjoy my videos, please keep subscribing to my channel. I'll continue to share my life and Yunnan-styled food in my uploads. Wish you have a happy life and enjoy tasty food every day
